  "commentary": "With SPX at 6586 in PIN regime, dealers are currently net buying as spot sits below the major negative gamma wall at 6570 (-27.1B), creating amplified downside pressure. The massive GEX surge (250%+ in 1-min) indicates heavy options flow is forcing dealers into aggressive hedging mode, likely accelerating any directional moves until price reaches the stabilizing zone between 6590-6600 where positive gamma kicks in.\n\nWatch 6570 as the critical amplification level - any break below triggers more dealer buying and downside acceleration, while a push back above 6590 should see increasing dealer resistance into the monster 6600 wall (+57.7B) where they'll aggressively sell rallies.",
